<html><head>
<TITLE>Daniel C. Palm</TITLE>
</head>

<body bgcolor=#ffffff>

<center>

   <hr noshade>

   <A HREF = "../bios.htm">Return to Staff and Fellows</A> ||
   <A HREF = "../index.html">Claremont Institute Home Page</A>

   <hr noshade>

   <H1>Daniel C. Palm</H1>

</CENTER>

Daniel C. Palm is Assistant Professor of Political Science, Azusa Pacific University, Azusa, 
California.  He holds a A.M. in Divinity from the University of Chicago Divinity School and the 
Ph.D. in Government from the Claremont Graduate School.  Dr. Palm is the author of "The 
Genesis of Strategic Military Planning in the U.S. Army and the General Staff" in Christopher C. 
Harmon and David Tucker, eds., <i>Statecraft and Power: Essays in Honor of Harold W. Rood</i> 
(University Press of America, 1994); <i>Homosexuality and Health: Some Public Health Facts 
American Schoolchildren Are Not Getting</i> (Claremont Institute, 1994), and co-editor of the 
forthcoming book, <i>On Faith and Free Government: The View from the Founding </i> 
(Claremont Institute, 1996).


<P>

